ing-capital swings or a capex year can distort a single ratio; the 5-yr median smooths it."},{"label":"Balance-sheet safety","value":0.62,"unit":"\u00d7 D/E","status":"weak","read":"Leveraged (D/E 0.62\u00d7, interest cover 1.9\u00d7).","meaning":"Latest debt-to-equity and interest coverage (EBIT \u00f7 interest) from the balance sheet.","why_useful":"Low debt and high interest cover let a business survive a downturn; high debt amplifies trouble.","why_it_can_fail":"Off-balance-sheet leases/guarantees aren't captured; a cash-rich firm can show low D/E yet still be risky elsewhere."},{"label":"Earnings momentum","value":-9.56,"unit":"% YoY","status":"weak","read":"Profit down 10% YoY (latest TTM).","meaning":"Trailing-twelve-month net profit vs the year-ago TTM (and whether the YoY rate is rising = 'accelerating').","why_useful":"Improving, accelerating earnings tend to drive re-rating; falling profit warns of a deteriorating business.","why_it_can_fail":"TTM can be lumpy for cyclicals/one-offs; cross-check the multi-year trend on the Fundamentals tab."}]},"valuation":{"ok":true,"is_bank":false,"pe_now":140.2,"pe_percentile":96.0,"median_pe":88.2,"earnings_yield_pct":0.71,"pb":8.06,"ev_ebitda":44.01,"quality_score":69.0,"pat_cagr_5y_pct":22.2,"peg":6.32,"cheapness":{"status":"weak","read":"P/E at the 96-percentile of its 10-yr range \u2014 expensive vs its own history."},"expectations":"At 140.2\u00d7 earnings for ~22% 5-yr profit CAGR, the market is paying \u22486.32\u00d7 growth (PEG). >2 = a lot already priced in; <1 = cheap if growth holds.","cyclical_caveat":null,"meaning":"P/E percentile = where today's price-to-earnings sits within the stock's own last-10-yr range (low = cheap vs its past). Paired with the Quality score and 5-yr profit growth so a cheap multiple is judged against business strength, not in isolation.","why_useful":"Cheapness only matters relative to quality and growth \u2014 a low P/E on a declining or peak-cyclical business is a trap, not a bargain.","why_it_can_fail":"P/E breaks for loss-makers / one-offs; for banks use P/B not EV/EBITDA; a multiple cheap vs history can stay cheap if the business has structurally de-rated."},"ownership":{"ok":true,"na":null,"holders":{"Promoter":{"periods":["Jun 2023","Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[40.32,40.31,40.31,40.31,39.87,39.79,39.72,39.72,39.65,38.22,38.19,38.17],"latest_pct":38.17,"chg_1y_pp":-1.55},"FII":{"periods":["Jun 2023","Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[24.2,29.69,28.29,25.98,28.42,26.39,28.56,27.05,28.59,30.61,26.98,23.96],"latest_pct":23.96,"chg_1y_pp":-3.09},"DII":{"periods":["Jun 2023","Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[12.66,13.07,14.67,15.83,15.73,17.8,19.11,19.42,17.82,20.2,23.86,27.92],"latest_pct":27.92,"chg_1y_pp":8.5},"Public":{"periods":["Jun 2023","Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[22.84,16.91,16.73,17.87,15.99,16.02,12.6,13.81,13.95,10.98,10.97,9.96],"latest_pct":9.96,"chg_1y_pp":-3.85}},"pledge":null,"events":[{"date":"02-Aug-2024","subject":"Annual General Meeting","materiality":"Med"}],"placeholders":[{"label":"Promoter pledge (detail)","note":"share-level pledge history \u2014 fetchable via NSE, deferred to MVP-2."},{"label":"Bulk / block deals","note":"large on-market trades \u2014 NSE feed, deferred to MVP-2."},{"label":"Insider / SAST disclosures","note":"promoter & designated-person dealings \u2014 deferred to MVP-2."},{"label":"Exchange announcements","note":"NSE/BSE filings stream \u2014 deferred to MVP-2."},{"label":"Results calendar","note":"next board-meeting / results date \u2014 deferred to MVP-2."},{"label":"Credit ratings","note":"rating-